### Optional Positional Parameters

Optional positional parameters are enclosed in square brackets `[]`. They must be nullable or have a default value.

```dart
void main() {
  greet('Alice');
  greet('Bob', 'Dr.');
  greet('Charlie', 'Prof.', 'PhD');
}

void greet(String name, [String? title, String? suffix]) {
  String full = '';
  if (title != null) full += '$title ';
  full += name;
  if (suffix != null) full += ', $suffix';
  print(full);
}
```

### Default Values for Optional Positional

```dart
void main() {
  calculate(10);        // Uses defaults
  calculate(10, 0.08);  // Custom tax rate
}

void calculate(double amount, [double taxRate = 0.05, bool includeService = false]) {
  double tax = amount * taxRate;
  double service = includeService ? amount * 0.1 : 0;
  double total = amount + tax + service;
  print('Total: \$${total.toStringAsFixed(2)}');
}
```

### Optional Named Parameters

Named parameters are always optional unless marked with `required`.

```dart
void main() {
  findPerson('Alice', age: 30);
  findPerson('Bob', city: 'New York', age: 25);
}

void findPerson(String name, {int? age, String? city}) {
  print('Searching for $name');
  if (age != null) print('Age: $age');
  if (city != null) print('City: $city');
}
```

### Combining Parameter Types

```dart
void main() {
  register('Alice', 'Smith',
    age: 30,
    email: 'alice@example.com',
  );
}

void register(
  String firstName,
  String lastName, [
  String? middleName,
]) {
  // Required first, optional positional, then named
}
```

| Parameter Type | Syntax | Example |
|---------------|--------|---------|
| Required positional | `Type name` | `String name` |
| Optional positional | `[Type? name]` | `[int? age]` |
| Optional named | `{Type? name}` | `{String? city}` |
| Required named | `{required Type name}` | `{required String email}` |

> **Key Point:** Optional positional parameters must come before named parameters. Required positional parameters must come before optional ones.

